                  <persName id="t18280911-100-person672">
                  GEORGE 
                  AVIS
               <interp inst="t18280911-100-person672" type="surname" value="AVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-100-person672" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-100-person672" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I have two certificates, which I have compared with the parish registers of Hackney and Chatham and found them correct - I apprehended the prisoner on the 27th of July; he was given in charge by his first wife, at Chelsea; I told him the charge - he said he had long expected it, and the reason he had married his second wife was that he had a respect for her, and did not wish her to be called a prostitute - his second wife is not here.</p>
               <p>JANE DAVIS. I was at Chatham, at the prisoner's marriage, on the 19th of September, 1812; he is a pensioner, and belonged to the same regiment as me - I witnessed the register: I never saw his second wife.</p>
               <p>The registers of the prisoner's marriage at Chatham, on the 19th of September, 1812, to 
