               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-100-person675">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COPEWELL
               <interp inst="t18280911-100-person675" type="surname" value="COPEWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-100-person675" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-100-person675" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a labourer. I have known the prisoner two or three years, and was at his marriage at St. George, Hanover-square - I knew his first wife, when she lived with him, about three years and a half ago; I saw her alive last Saturday week; she was a neighbour's child - this prosecution is not at her instance.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He urged me to marry several times; I objected to it, but he persuaded me - my first wife and I agreed to separate and never speak: I never could live at peace with her; I understood she had been married before, but the witnesses who had informed me of it were dead - she has prostituted herself in my own bed; she had money allowed by gentlemen she formerly lived with; she has had 4s. a week from me, and obtained money from three or four different parishes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-100-person676">
                  ANN 
                  RUST
               <interp inst="t18280911-100-person676" type="surname" value="RUST"></interp>
